<p>Lots of registry changes require you to logoff an logon again to apply the changes. However, if you press the <code>Apply</code> button in the <code>Appearance and Personalisation</code> section, the appearance refreshes without needing to log out:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.imgur.com/JXLethh.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.imgur.com/JXLethh.png" alt="Apply Button"></a></p>  <p>I wonder if Windows provides an API for this function so that it can be called programmatically without signing out?</p>  <p>It would be much easier to test some settings if one could just run a simple console application or a PowerShell script to commit the changes.</p>